title: Tuesday injuries: Kuechly, Lynch on track to play Sunday; Julio Jones a queston
text:
Panthers LB Luke Kuechly has been cleared from concussion protocol. (Photo: Phil Sears, USA TODAY)
2 CONNECT 25 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE Both the Carolina Panthers and Seattle Seahawks received some good news on the injury front before their showdown in Seattle on Sunday.
Carolina Panthers linebacker Luke Kuechly has been released from concussion protocol and can practice this week, according to several reports He has not practiced or played in a game since suffering a concussion in the season opener against Jacksonville.
Coach Pete Carroll said RB Marshawn Lynch (hamstring) is on track to return to practice on Thursday. Lynch missed the past two games with hamstring issues.
In other injury news:
- Atlanta WR Julio Jones (hamstring, toe) missed practice Monday and, according to ESPN, the Falcons are "uncertain" if he can play Thursday night vs. New Orleans.
